    <!-- OBJECT -->
    <div id="object">
        <h2>OBJECT:</h2>
        <div class="rules-box">
            <ul>
                <li>This game follows and enhances Karma’s style of “Card Shedding” Play, meaning Players have to get rid of their Cards and the Game continues until the last Player is left – who is the only Loser.</li>
                <li>For those wanting a more Decisive Victory, see: Scoring – Winning The Game.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <a href="#top" class="shortcut-link">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>

    <!-- SETUP -->
    <div id="setup">
        <h2>SETUP:</h2>
        <div class="rules-box">
            <ol>
                <li>As a group choose whether to use the Core Extension and any Optional Expansion or Coloured Extension Packs [compare Soloverse Game Notes: First Play Recommendations].
                    <div class="note-box">
                        <strong>NOTE:</strong> If You have added any Optional Expansions, check if they have any Additional Setup Rules.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>Choose who Deals first [alternate the Dealer clockwise after each game].</li>
                <li>Shuffle the Deck and Deal one Card Face-Down to all Players, repeating until everyone has 6 Cards Face-Down in front of them.</li>
                <li>Then do so again but with Face-Up Cards and place them on top of Player’s Face-Down Cards.
                    <div class="note-box">
                        <strong>NOTE:</strong> Your Face-Up and Face-Down Cards now form Your “Table Cards”.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>Next, Deal 15 Cards to all Players, one Card at a time to form Player’s Hands.</li>
                <li>And finally, place the Deck in the middle of the Table, leaving room for the Discards to go beside it.</li>
                <li>Place the Direction Of Play [Blue/Clockwise Side] and the Play To The Side Of The Discards Chaos Cards Face-Up on either side of the Discards, where everyone can see them [Remember to Flip the Direction Of Play Chaos Card it every time a Reverse Effect Activates].</li>
                <li>If using the Core Extension, place Recycle Chaos Card Face-Up next to the Deck and Discards, where all Players can reach it.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        <a href="#top" class="shortcut-link">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>

		<div class="image-container">
